abstract: The outlook for last-generation tech companies is often grim as their products become commonplace, rivals find alternatives and margins shrink.
snippet: The outlook for last-generation tech companies is often grim as their products become commonplace, rivals find alternatives and margins shrink.
lead_paragraph: Intel and Cisco Systems are facing divergent futures. Intel is swallowing its pride and licensing intellectual property from its chip-making rival ARM. Cisco is planning to cut 7 percent of its workers. Intel may have the strong hand.

headline.main: Intel Seems to Have a Stronger Hand Than Cisco Systems
